{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0368eng","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0368ENG","gazette":"Official Journal of the European Union","title":"EU Commission acts against unfairly subsidised imports of mobile access equipment from China","date":"01 Mayıs 2025","bodyHtml":"<p>The European Commission has published <a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=OJ:L_202500796\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Regulation No. 2025/796,</a> which imposes definitive countervailing duties on mobile access equipment (MAE) imported from China and amends the anti-dumping duty rates, to enter into force as of April 26, 2025.</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Product scope definition of the measure:</span></p><p>Self-propelled mobile access equipment designed for the lifting of persons, with a maximum working height of at least 6 meters, as well as their pre-assembled or ready-to-assemble components (such as chassis / tower or turntable / platforms or baskets / lifting mechanism for mobile access equipment, including telescopic and/or articulated booms for telescopic boom platforms, articulated boom platforms or vertical mast platforms (with or without booms), and scissor arms for scissor lift platforms).</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Relevant TARIC codes:</span></p><p>8427 10 10 10, 8427 20 19 10, 8428 90 90 20, 8431 20 00 60, and 8431 39 00 10.</p><p>The countervailing duty rates have been set as follows:</p><div id=\"001.002\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: medium;\"><p class=\"oj-normal\" style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: 1.3em; text-align: justify;\"><br></p><table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" class=\"oj-table\" style=\"border-color: black; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px; font-size: inherit; width: inherit;\"><colgroup><col width=\"35%\"><col width=\"38%